---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">About POTM</h1>

  <div class="mt-6 space-y-6 text-gray-700">
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">What is POTM?</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        POTM (Player of the Match) is a simple voting app for sports teams.
        After a match, share a link with your team and let everyone vote for
        their player of the match — no sign-up required for voters.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">How it works</h2>

      <h3 class="mt-4 text-base font-medium text-gray-900">For admins (setting up)</h3>
      <ol class="mt-2 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>
          <strong>Create an account</strong> — Sign in with Google to manage your squads.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Create a squad</strong> — Name your team, add a description and optional header image.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Add players</strong> — Add your team's players to the squad roster.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Create a fixture</strong> — Add the opponent, select players, and optionally add details (location, kick-off, kit) and a deadline. You can open voting when you create it or later from the fixture page.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open voting and share the link</strong> — When you're ready, open voting (set a deadline), copy the fixture link, and share it with your team (WhatsApp, email, etc.).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>View results</strong> — Admins see live results at any time. You can close voting early and then show results when ready. After the deadline (or when you show results), everyone can see the winner(s). Joint POTM is supported if players tie on votes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Postponed or cancelled</strong> — If a game doesn't go ahead, edit the fixture and set status to Postponed or Cancelled. The fixture keeps a clear badge and no voting; you can later set a new date and status back to Scheduled, or leave it and create a new fixture for the rearranged match.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h3 class="mt-4 text-base font-medium text-gray-900">For voters (no account needed)</h3>
      <ol class="mt-2 list-decimal space-y-2 pl-6">
        <li>
          <strong>Get the link</strong> — An admin shares the fixture link with you.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Open the link</strong> — You see the fixture details (opponent, date, venue, kit, etc.). If voting isn't open yet, you'll see a message to check back later.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Vote</strong> — When voting is open, enter your name, pick your player of the match, and submit. One vote per person (we use a cookie to prevent double voting).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>After voting</strong> — You see a thanks message. Results and the winner(s) are visible to everyone after the voting deadline or when an admin has shown results.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Multi-admin support</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Invite other managers to help run your squad. Admins can manage players,
        create fixtures, and view results. The squad owner can invite and remove
        admins.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900">Open source</h2>
      <p class="mt-2">
        POTM is open source. Check out the code on
        <a
          href="https://github.com/leggetter/potm"
          class="text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700 underline"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
